## Ethernet Basics
- Ethernet is a coillection of network protocols and standards
- defined by IEEE 802.3 standard
- these speeds are measured in bits per second not bytes per second, i used to get this mixed up. (BPS)
- 1 bit = a 0 or 1 
- 1 byte is 8 bits

## Speeds

size             Bits
1 kilobit (KB) = 1,000
1 Megabit (MB) = 1,000,000
1 Gigabit (GB) = 1,000,000,000
1 Terabit (TB) = 1,000,000,000,000


## Copper Ethernet standards
speed       name             standard      max distance
10 MBPS     ethernet         802.3i        100M
100 MBPS    Fast Ethernet    802.3u        100m
1 GBPS      Gigabit Ethernet 802.3ab       100m
10 GBPS      10 Gig Ethernet 802.3 an     100m


## UTP Cables
- Unshielded twisted Pair
- 10/100base-T = 2 pairs (4 wires)
-1000/10GBASE-T = 4 pairs (8 wires)

## Cable Types
- Straight - through cable - connects different devices
( pc to switch, router to switch)
- Crossover cable - connects similar devices
( pc to pc, switch to switch)
- Auto MDI X - modern devices auto detect which cable is neeeded

## fiber optic cables
- uses light instead of electrical signals
- Needs SFP (small form-factor pluggable) transceiver to connect to switches/routers

### single mode
- laser based  transmitter
- longest distance
- most EXPENSIVE
- narrow

### Multimode
- Wider
- LED based transmitter
- Shorter than single mode
- Cheaper than single mode


## fiber optic standards
standard       speed       mode                      max distance
1000BASE-LX    1 GBPS      multi/single mode         550m 
10GBASE-SR     10 GBPS     Multimode                 400M
10GBASE-LR     10 GBPS     single                    10 Km
10GBASE-ER     10 GBPS     Single                    30km











